title: Stores can't keep Meghan Markle's $32 Madewell earrings in stock
text:
It's official: The Duke and Duchess of Sussex's 10-day royal tour of Africa came to an end on Wednesday, closing out a week and a half of moving speeches, high-profile engagements, baby Archie sightings and of course, impeccable royal style.

Meghan Markle proved once again that she's an expert in high-low fashion by showcasing a chic mix of high designer buys with more affordable gems. It's a trend she followed through from her first engagement to her last, when she visited Tembisa with Prince Harry to learn more about the township's initiatives in wake of the unemployment crisis.

The mom-of-one looked gorgeous as ever, opting for a white shirtdress by South African designer Hannah Lavery. She paired the look with Stuart Weitzman pumps and, yes, $32 earrings from Madewell, proving that good style comes at many different price points.

The brand's tassel and stone earrings are so popular, in fact, that they've already sold out on Madewell and Nordstrom's website -- but they are still available on Shopbop for $32 in blue!
